Given a binary string s ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äãwithout leading zeros, return true‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã if s contains at most one contiguous segment of ones. Otherwise, return false.

 

Example 1:

Input: s = "1001"
Output: false
Explanation: The ones do not form a contiguous segment.
Example 2:

Input: s = "110"
Output: true
 

Constraints:

1 <= s.length <= 100
s[i]‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã is either '0' or '1'.
s[0] is '1'.
 
Code : // O(n)

Approach 1:

class Solution {
    public boolean checkOnesSegment(String s) {
        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '1') {
                count++; // new segment
                while (i < s.length() && s.charAt(i) == '1') {
                    i++;
                }
                i--; // adjust for for-loop increment
            }

            if (count > 1) {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
}

Approach 2:

class Solution {
    public boolean checkOnesSegment(String s) {
        return !s.contains("01");
    }
}

